# Interaction Specifications - Paramedic One-Page Website

## Overview
This document details all user interactions, flows, and animations for the paramedic website.

---

## 1. Smooth Scroll Navigation

### Trigger
Click on nav link in header or footer.

### Flow
1. User clicks nav link (e.g., "#news")
2. Prevent default anchor jump
3. Get target element position (document.getElementById('news').offsetTop)
4. Calculate scroll position (subtract header height: 72px)
5. Animate scroll to position over 0.6s

### Code Pattern (JavaScript)
```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
  anchor.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const target = document.querySelector(this.getAttribute('href'));
    if (target) {
      const headerOffset = 72;
      const elementPosition = target.getBoundingClientRect().top;
      const offsetPosition = elementPosition + window.pageYOffset - headerOffset;
      window.scrollTo({ top: offsetPosition, behavior: 'smooth' });
    }
  });
});
```

### States
- **Default**: Link color #1D3557
- **Hover**: Color #E63946, underline animates in from left
- **Active/Scrolled**: Current section highlighted

---

## 2. Mobile Navigation Drawer

### Trigger
Click hamburger icon in mobile header.

### Flow
1. User clicks hamburger button
2. Add class `open` to drawer
3. Set aria-hidden to false
4. Trap focus inside drawer
5. Prevent body scroll

### Close Flow
1. Click close button, overlay, or press Escape
2. Remove `open` class
3. Return focus to hamburger button
4. Restore body scroll

### States
- **Closed**: translateX(100%), hidden from accessibility tree
- **Opening**: translateX(0), overlay fade in 0.2s
- **Open**: Visible, focus trapped

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const drawer = document.querySelector('.mobile-nav');
const overlay = document.querySelector('.mobile-nav__overlay');
const hamburger = document.querySelector('.hamburger');
const closeBtn = document.querySelector('.mobile-nav__close');

function openDrawer() {
  drawer.classList.add('open');
  overlay.classList.add('active');
  document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
  closeBtn.focus();
}

function closeDrawer() {
  drawer.classList.remove('open');
  overlay.classList.remove('active');
  document.body.style.overflow = '';
  hamburger.focus();
}

hamburger.addEventListener('click', openDrawer);
closeBtn.addEventListener('click', closeDrawer);
overlay.addEventListener('click', closeDrawer);
document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  if (e.key === 'Escape') closeDrawer();
});
```

---

## 3. Tab Navigation (Database Section)

### Trigger
Click on tab button.

### Flow
1. User clicks tab button
2. Remove `active` class from all tabs
3. Add `active` class to clicked tab
4. Hide all tab panels
5. Show corresponding panel
6. Update aria-selected on tabs

### States
- **Inactive tab**: Default styling, aria-selected="false"
- **Active tab**: Bold, border accent, aria-selected="true"
- **Inactive panel**: display: none
- **Active panel**: display: block, fade in

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.pos-tab');
const panels = document.querySelectorAll('.pos-tab-panel');

tabs.forEach(tab => {
  tab.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const targetPanel = tab.dataset.panel;

    tabs.forEach(t => {
      t.classList.remove('active');
      t.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'false');
    });

    panels.forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));

    tab.classList.add('active');
    tab.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'true');
    document.getElementById(targetPanel).classList.add('active');
  });
});
```

---

## 4. Database Search

### Trigger
User types in search input or selects filter.

### Flow
1. User types search query (debounce 300ms)
2. Filter displayed results based on query
3. Show "No results" message if empty
4. Highlight matching text in results

### Validation
- Minimum 2 characters to search
- Case-insensitive matching
- Search across: name, aliases, class, indications

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const searchInput = document.querySelector('.database-search input');
const categorySelect = document.querySelector('.database-search select');
const cards = document.querySelectorAll('.drug-card');

function filterCards() {
  const query = searchInput.value.toLowerCase();
  const category = categorySelect.value;

  cards.forEach(card => {
    const text = card.textContent.toLowerCase();
    const matchesSearch = text.includes(query);
    const matchesCategory = category === 'All Categories' || 
      card.dataset.category === category;

    card.style.display = matchesSearch && matchesCategory ? '' : 'none';
  });
}

let debounce;
searchInput.addEventListener('input', () => {
  clearTimeout(debounce);
  debounce = setTimeout(filterCards, 300);
});
categorySelect.addEventListener('change', filterCards);
```

---

## 5. Scroll-triggered Animations

### Trigger
Element enters viewport (20% visible).

### Flow
1. Create Intersection Observer
2. Observe all animated elements
3. When element crosses threshold:
   - Add class `animated`
   - Apply animation
4. Once animated, unobserve element

### Animation Classes
```css
.fade-up {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(30px);
  transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease;
}

.fade-up.animated {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}

.fade-in {
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 0.6s ease;
}

.fade-in.animated {
  opacity: 1;
}

.stagger-1 { transition-delay: 0.1s; }
.stagger-2 { transition-delay: 0.2s; }
.stagger-3 { transition-delay: 0.3s; }
.stagger-4 { transition-delay: 0.4s; }
.stagger-5 { transition-delay: 0.5s; }
.stagger-6 { transition-delay: 0.6s; }
```

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const observerOptions = {
  root: null,
  rootMargin: '0px',
  threshold: 0.2
};

const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      entry.target.classList.add('animated');
      observer.unobserve(entry.target);
    }
  });
}, observerOptions);

document.querySelectorAll('.fade-up, .fade-in').forEach(el => {
  observer.observe(el);
});
```

---

## 6. Header Scroll Effect

### Trigger
User scrolls past hero section.

### Flow
1. Listen to scroll event (throttled)
2. If scrollY > 100:
   - Add class `scrolled` to header
   - Add shadow
3. Else:
   - Remove `scrolled` class
   - Remove shadow

### States
- **Top**: Transparent/solid white, no shadow
- **Scrolled**: White background, shadow visible

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const header = document.querySelector('.site-header');
let lastScroll = 0;

window.addEventListener('scroll', throttle(() => {
  const currentScroll = window.pageYOffset;

  if (currentScroll > 100) {
    header.classList.add('scrolled');
  } else {
    header.classList.remove('scrolled');
  }

  lastScroll = currentScroll;
}, 100));

function throttle(func, limit) {
  let inThrottle;
  return function() {
    if (!inThrottle) {
      func.apply(this, arguments);
      inThrottle = true;
      setTimeout(() => inThrottle = false, limit);
    }
  };
}
```

---

## 7. Form Validation

### Trigger
User submits form or blurs field.

### Flow
1. On blur: Validate single field
2. On submit: Validate all fields
3. If invalid:
   - Add `error` class to input
   - Show error message
   - Prevent submission
4. If valid:
   - Remove error state
   - Allow submission

### Validation Rules
| Field | Rules |
|-------|-------|
| Email | Required, valid email format |
| Name | Required, min 2 characters |
| Search | Min 2 characters (for search) |
| Newsletter | Required, valid email |

### Error Messages
- Required: "This field is required"
- Email: "Please enter a valid email address"
- Min length: "Must be at least X characters"

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const form = document.querySelector('.newsletter-form');

function validateField(field) {
  const value = field.value.trim();
  let error = null;

  if (field.required && !value) {
    error = 'This field is required';
  } else if (field.type === 'email' && value) {
    const emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
    if (!emailRegex.test(value)) {
      error = 'Please enter a valid email address';
    }
  }

  const errorEl = field.parentElement.querySelector('.pos-form-error');

  if (error) {
    field.classList.add('error');
    if (errorEl) errorEl.textContent = error;
    return false;
  } else {
    field.classList.remove('error');
    if (errorEl) errorEl.textContent = '';
    return true;
  }
}

form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  const fields = form.querySelectorAll('[required]');
  let isValid = true;

  fields.forEach(field => {
    if (!validateField(field)) isValid = false;
  });

  if (isValid) {
    // Submit form
    console.log('Form submitted');
  }
});
```

---

## 8. Button Loading State

### Trigger
Form submission or async action initiated.

### Flow
1. User clicks button
2. Add `loading` class to button
3. Disable button
4. Show spinner
5. Hide button text (visually)
6. On complete: Remove loading state

### Visual
- Button: Disabled appearance
- Spinner: CSS-only rotating icon
- Text: visiblity hidden or replaced

### Code Pattern
```javascript
function setLoading(button, isLoading) {
  if (isLoading) {
    button.classList.add('loading');
    button.disabled = true;
  } else {
    button.classList.remove('loading');
    button.disabled = false;
  }
}
```

```css
.pos-button.loading .pos-button__text {
  visibility: hidden;
}

.pos-button.loading .pos-button__loader {
  display: block;
}

.pos-button__loader {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  margin: -10px 0 0 -10px;
  border: 2px solid currentColor;
  border-right-color: transparent;
  border-radius: 50%;
  animation: spin 0.75s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes spin {
  to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}
```

---

## 9. Card Hover Interactions

### Trigger
Mouse enters card element.

### Flow
1. Mouse enters card
2. Add `hover` class
3. Apply hover styles:
   - Transform translateY(-4px)
   - Shadow elevation increase
4. Mouse leaves: Remove class

### Affected Components
- News cards
- Event cards
- Course cards
- Drug reference cards

### Visual Specifications
```css
.pos-card {
  transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
}

.pos-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
}
```

---

## 10. Newsletter Signup Flow

### Trigger
User enters email and clicks subscribe.

### Flow
1. User enters email
2. Validates email format
3. Clicks subscribe
4. Shows loading state
5. On success:
   - Shows success message
   - Clears form
   - Auto-hide after 5 seconds
6. On error:
   - Shows error message
   - Keeps form data

### States
- **Default**: Email input + Subscribe button
- **Loading**: Button spinner
- **Success**: Green checkmark + "Thanks for subscribing!"
- **Error**: Red message + form preserved

### Code Pattern
```javascript
const newsletterForm = document.querySelector('.newsletter-form');

newsletterForm.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  const email = newsletterForm.querySelector('input').value;
  const button = newsletterForm.querySelector('button');

  setLoading(button, true);

  try {
    // Simulate API call
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));

    showMessage('success', 'Thanks for subscribing!');
    newsletterForm.reset();
  } catch (error) {
    showMessage('error', 'Something went wrong. Please try again.');
  } finally {
    setLoading(button, false);
  }
});

function showMessage(type, text) {
  // Create or update message element
  const existing = document.querySelector('.form-message');
  if (existing) existing.remove();

  const message = document.createElement('div');
  message.className = `form-message form-message--${type}`;
  message.textContent = text;
  newsletterForm.appendChild(message);

  if (type === 'success') {
    setTimeout(() => message.remove(), 5000);
  }
}
```

---

## 11. Keyboard Navigation

### Requirements
1. **Tab order**: Logical flow (header → content → footer)
2. **Skip link**: "Skip to main content" at top
3. **Focus visible**: 2px outline on all interactive elements
4. **Escape**: Close modals/drawers
5. **Arrow keys**: Navigate tabs and menus

### Skip Link Implementation
```html
<a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
```

```css
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  left: 0;
  background: #E63946;
  color: white;
  padding: 8px;
  z-index: 1000;
  transition: top 0.2s;
}

.skip-link:focus {
  top: 0;
}
```

### Focus Styles
```css
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #1D3557;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

button:focus-visible,
a:focus-visible,
input:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #1D3557;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

---

## 12. Accordion (Expandable Details)

### Trigger
Click on accordion header.

### Flow
1. Click header
2. Toggle `expanded` class
3. Animate content height from 0 to auto
4. Update aria-expanded attribute

### Structure
```html
<details class="accordion">
  <summary class="accordion__header">
    <span>Drug Name</span>
    <svg class="accordion__icon" icon="chevron"></svg>
  </summary>
  <div class="accordion__content">
    Detailed information...
  </div>
</details>
```

### Code Pattern
```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('details.accordion').forEach(detail => {
  detail.addEventListener('toggle', () => {
    const header = detail.querySelector('.accordion__header');
    header.setAttribute('aria-expanded', detail.open);
  });
});
```

```css
.accordion__content {
  max-height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
}

details.accordion[open] .accordion__content {
  max-height: 500px; /* Or calculate via JS */
}

.accordion__icon {
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
}

details.accordion[open] .accordion__icon {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}
```

/* ================================================
   ParamedicHub - Main Stylesheet
   "Emanating with Life" Color Palette
   ================================================ */

/* CSS Variables - Color Palette */
:root {
  /* Primary Colors */
  --color-emergency-red: #E63946;
  --color-medical-blue: #1D3557;
  --color-life-green: #2A9D8F;
  --color-warm-orange: #F4A261;

  /* Background & Text */
  --color-background: #FAFBFC;
  --color-text: #1A1A2E;
  --color-text-light: #6C757D;
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;

  /* Status Colors */
  --color-success: #2A9D8F;
  --color-warning: #F4A261;
  --color-error: #E63946;
  --color-info: #457B9D;

  /* Shadows */
  --shadow-sm: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  --shadow-lg: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  --shadow-xl: 0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);

  /* Typography */
  --font-primary: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  --font-size-xs: 0.75rem;
  --font-size-sm: 0.875rem;
  --font-size-base: 1rem;
  --font-size-lg: 1.125rem;
  --font-size-xl: 1.25rem;
  --font-size-2xl: 1.5rem;
  --font-size-3xl: 1.875rem;
  --font-size-4xl: 2.25rem;
  --font-size-5xl: 3rem;

  /* Spacing */
  --spacing-xs: 0.25rem;
  --spacing-sm: 0.5rem;
  --spacing-md: 1rem;
  --spacing-lg: 1.5rem;
  --spacing-xl: 2rem;
  --spacing-2xl: 3rem;
  --spacing-3xl: 4rem;
  --spacing-4xl: 5rem;

  /* Border Radius */
  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 8px;
  --radius-lg: 12px;
  --radius-xl: 16px;
  --radius-full: 9999px;

  /* Transitions */
  --transition-fast: 0.15s ease;
  --transition-base: 0.2s ease;
  --transition-slow: 0.3s ease;
  --transition-smooth: 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);

  /* Container */
  --container-max: 1200px;
  --container-padding: 1rem;

  /* Header */
  --header-height: 72px;
}

/* Reset & Base Styles */
*,
*::before,
*::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

html {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
  font-size: 16px;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-primary);
  font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--color-text);
  background-color: var(--color-background);
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  overflow-x: hidden;
}

/* Accessibility - Focus Styles */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-medical-blue);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

button:focus-visible,
a:focus-visible,
input:focus-visible,
select:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-medical-blue);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Skip Link */
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -100%;
  left: 0;
  background: var(--color-emergency-red);
  color: var(--color-white);
  padding: var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-md);
  z-index: 10000;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: top var(--transition-fast);
}

.skip-link:focus {
  top: 0;
}

/* Typography */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: var(--color-medical-blue);
}

h1 { font-size: var(--font-size-4xl); }
h2 { font-size: var(--font-size-3xl); }
h3 { font-size: var(--font-size-2xl); }
h4 { font-size: var(--font-size-xl); }

p {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

a {
  color: var(--color-medical-blue);
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: color var(--transition-fast);
}

a:hover {
  color: var(--color-emergency-red);
}

/* Container */
.container {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--container-max);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 var(--container-padding);
}

/* ================================================
   Navigation
   ================================================ */
.site-header {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  height: var(--header-height);
  background: var(--color-white);
  z-index: 1000;
  transition: box-shadow var(--transition-base);
}

.site-header.scrolled {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
}

.header-inner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  height: 100%;
  max-width: var(--container-max);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 var(--container-padding);
}

.logo {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-weight: 800;
  color: var(--color-medical-blue);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.logo-icon {
  width: 36px;
  height: 36px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-emergency-red), var(--color-warm-orange));
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: var(--color-white);
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
}

.nav-links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--spacing-xl);
  list-style: none;
}

.nav-links a {
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-text);
  position: relative;
  padding: var(--spacing-xs) 0;
}

.nav-links a::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: var(--color-emergency-red);
  transition: width var(--transition-base);
}

.nav-links a:hover::after,
.nav-links a.active::after {
  width: 100%;
}

.nav-links a:hover,
.nav-links a.active {
  color: var(--color-emergency-red);
}

/* Mobile Navigation */
.hamburger {
  display: none;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  background: none;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: var(--spacing-sm);
  gap: 5px;
}

.hamburger span {
  display: block;
  width: 24px;
  height: 2px;
  background: var(--color-text);
  transition: transform var(--transition-base), opacity var(--transition-base);
}

.hamburger.active span:nth-child(1) {
  transform: translateY(7px) rotate(45deg);
}

.hamburger.active span:nth-child(2) {
  opacity: 0;
}

.hamburger.active span:nth-child(3) {
  transform: translateY(-7px) rotate(-45deg);
}

.mobile-nav {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  right: -280px;
  width: 280px;
  height: 100vh;
  background: var(--color-white);
  z-index: 1001;
  transition: right var(--transition-smooth);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
}

.mobile-nav.open {
  right: 0;
}

.mobile-nav__header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.mobile-nav__close {
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  background: none;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
  color: var(--color-text);
}

.mobile-nav__links {
  list-style: none;
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
}

.mobile-nav__links li {
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
}

.mobile-nav__links a {
  display: block;
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-text);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  transition: background var(--transition-fast), color var(--transition-fast);
}

.mobile-nav__links a:hover {
  background: var(--color-background);
  color: var(--color-emergency-red);
}

.mobile-nav__overlay {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  z-index: 1000;
  opacity: 0;
  visibility: hidden;
  transition: opacity var(--transition-base), visibility var(--transition-base);
}

.mobile-nav__overlay.active {
  opacity: 1;
  visibility: visible;
}

/* ================================================
   Hero Section
   ================================================ */
.hero {
  min-height: 100vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  position: relative;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-medical-blue) 0%, var(--color-life-green) 100%);
  padding-top: var(--header-height);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.hero::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  background: rgba(29, 53, 87, 0.7);
}

.hero-content {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  text-align: center;
  max-width: 800px;
  padding: var(--spacing-2xl);
}

.hero-eyebrow {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  font-weight: 600;
